n":"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"The non-CQT portion routinely under-tiles\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16495490/159599961-9ef21996-612b-4cdf-9a37-0870d260edd4.png\" width=\"700\">\r\n\r\nso parts of input are attenuated - bad news where low frequencies matter, which is always for second-order scattering (and JTFS). Increasing the number of said filters fixes this: `num_intermediate = Q - 1` -> `Q` (`filter_bank.compute_params_filterbank`):\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16495490/159600274-fd41d283-a8f6-4fb5-b44c-fd4f47d74baf.png\" width=\"700\">\r\n\r\nNote for `Q=1` we added an entire wavelet while changing nothing else, and it fit right in, suggesting we're missing an entire wavelet.\r\n\r\nWorst case on performance is with `Q=1`; one extra wavelet at second order with `Q2=1` is a small compute overhead since it's a large kernel convolution (max stride), and not a memory overhead since we can discard it if we wish. Larger `Q` has negligible overhead in any sense. I recommend this as the new default.","closed_by":{"login":"MuawizChaudhary","id":39755015,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM5NzU1MDE1","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/39755015?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary","html_url":"https://github.com/MuawizChaudhary","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/MuawizChaudhary/events{/privacy}","received_events_